### <%= @class_header %> : get_facing_away()
``` lua
local <%= @variable_text %>	-- example <%= @variable_text %>
local <%= @variable_text %>_facing = 	<%= @variable_text %>:get_facing_away()
```
Returns the <%= @link_direction %> *opposite* of the direction this <%= @class_name %> is facing.<br>
_i.e. if the <%= @class_name %> is facing_ **`Left`**_, it will return_ **`Right`**_, etc._

#### Function Call
`<%= @variable_text %>:get_facing_away()`

#### Return Value
<%= @link_facing %>
